.TH TB 1 "December 2025" "ToolBox 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
tb \- context-aware command aliasing for developers
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B tb
[\fIOPTIONS\fR]
.I COMMAND
[\fIARGS\fR...]
.br
.B tb
\fB\-\-help\fR
.br
.B tb
\fB\-\-version\fR
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B ToolBox (tb)
is a context-aware CLI tool that provides intelligent command shortcuts based on your project type. Instead of remembering different commands for different projects (npm run build, go build, cargo build, etc.), you can use a consistent interface like
.B tb build
and ToolBox automatically runs the correct command for your current project.
.PP
ToolBox detects your project type by scanning for marker files (package.json, go.mod, Cargo.toml, etc.) and maps generic commands to project-specific commands. It's extensible through YAML configuration and a plugin system.
.PP
.B Important:
ToolBox flags must come before the command name. Any flags after the command name are passed to the underlying command.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-\-config " " \fIFILE\fR
Specify config file (default: .toolbox.yaml or ~/.toolbox/config.yaml)
.TP
.BR \-\-context " " \fICONTEXT\fR
Force a specific context (node, go, python, rust, etc.)
.TP
.BR \-\-dry\-run
Print command without executing it
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-help
Display help information
.TP
.BR \-\-timeout " " \fIDURATION\fR
Command execution timeout (default: 10m0s)
.TP
.BR \-\-verbose
Enable verbose output showing context detection (note: -v is not supported to avoid conflicts with command arguments)
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B completion
Generate shell completion script for bash, zsh, fish, or powershell
.TP
.B help
Show help for a specific command in the current or specified context
.TP
.B plugin
Manage ToolBox plugins (list, info, contexts)
.TP
.B status
Show current context, available commands, and other detected contexts
.PP
Additionally, context-specific commands are available based on the detected project type. Common commands include:
.TP
.B build
Build the project
.TP
.B test
Run tests
.TP
.B start
Start the application
.TP
.B dev
Start development server
.TP
.B lint
Run linter
.TP
.B fmt
Format code
.TP
.B install
Install dependencies
.TP
.B run
Run the application
.PP
See
.B CONTEXTS
below for context-specific commands.
.SH CONTEXTS
ToolBox supports multiple project contexts out of the box:
.SS Node.js (node)
Detected by:
.B package.json
.br
Commands: build, test, start, dev, lint, install
.SS Go (go)
Detected by:
.B go.mod
.br
Commands: build, test, run, install, lint, fmt
.SS Python (python)
Detected by:
.B pyproject.toml
or
.B requirements.txt
.br
Commands: test, lint, fmt, install, run
.SS Rust (rust)
Detected by:
.B Cargo.toml
.br
Commands: build, test, run, lint, fmt, install
.SS Make (make)
Detected by:
.B Makefile
.br
Commands: build, test, clean
.SS Docker (docker)
Detected by:
.B Dockerfile
or
.B docker-compose.yml
.br
Commands: build, up, down, logs, ps, shell
.SS Kubernetes (kubernetes)
Detected by:
.B *.yaml
or
.B *.yml
files with Kubernetes resources
.br
Commands: apply, delete, get-pods, get-all, logs, describe, exec
.SS Ubuntu Packaging (ubuntu-packaging)
Detected by:
.B debian/control
or
.B debian/changelog
.br
Commands: gbranch, ppa-status, dch-auto, ubuild, sb-auto, dput-auto, and more
.SH CONFIGURATION
ToolBox uses YAML configuration files to define contexts and commands. Configuration is loaded in the following priority order:
.PP
1. File specified with \fB\-\-config\fR flag
.br
2. \fB.toolbox.yaml\fR in current directory
.br
3. \fB~/.toolbox/config.yaml\fR in home directory
.br
4. Built-in defaults
.PP
Example configuration:
.PP
.in +4n
.nf
contexts:
  node:
    commands:
      build: "npm run build:prod"
      test: "npm test -- --coverage"
      deploy: "npm run deploy"
  
  custom:
    commands:
      up: "docker-compose up -d"
      down: "docker-compose down"
.fi
.in
.PP
See
.BR tb-config (5)
for detailed configuration documentation.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B tb build
Build the current project using the appropriate build command for the detected context
.TP
.B tb --dry-run test
Show what test command would be executed without running it (note: tb flags before command)
.TP
.B tb test -v -race
Run tests with -v and -race flags passed to the underlying test command
.TP
.B tb --context python build
Force the use of Python context commands regardless of detected project type
.TP
.B tb help build
Show help for the 'build' command in the current context
.TP
.B tb status
Show current context and all available commands in that context
.TP
.B tb plugin list
List all available plugins and their status
.TP
.B tb \-\-version
Show version information
.TP
.B tb completion bash > /etc/bash_completion.d/tb
Generate and install bash completion script
.SH FILES
.TP
.I .toolbox.yaml
Project-specific configuration file
.TP
.I ~/.toolbox/config.yaml
User-specific global configuration
.TP
.I ~/.cache/toolbox/
Cache directory for temporary files (e.g., extracted scripts)
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success
.TP
.B 1
General error (command not found, execution failed, etc.)
.TP
.B 2
Configuration error
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B HOME
Used to locate the user's configuration directory (~/.toolbox/)
.TP
.B PATH
Used to locate external commands executed by ToolBox
